<typeStatus box="[456,514,398,422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="293">types</typeStatus>
were collected by sifting the roots of grass and herbs in the shade of shrubs and trees on slopes with oak and juniper at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[994,1126,429,453]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.05" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="293" unit="m" value="705.0" valueMax="850.0" valueMin="560.0">
<elevation box="[994,1126,429,453]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.05" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="293" unit="m" value="705.0" valueMax="850.0" valueMin="560.0">560-850 m</elevation>
</quantity>
. The locality near Hopurlu is shown in 
<figureCitation box="[576,658,461,485]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[247,279,847,869]" captionTargetBox="[247,1131,174,837]" captionTargetId="figure-226@6.[247,1131,174,837]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 14: Type locality of Sunius brevipennis sp. n. (photo by P. WUNDERLE)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4751777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4751777/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="293">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
